g.text: You: "The fire guy. Some kids told me about a *guy* here. A guy who made a fire."
Cuno: "All right." He claps his hands. "We're on to something -- Cuno meant fire guy too."
Microgrid Generator: There's a red starter switch on the side of the cylinder and a start rope on the other side -- Cuno flicks the switch.
You: Put your hand on the machine.
Microgrid Generator: It's cold. Rust flakes off and sticks to your palm.
Microgrid Generator: The recoil start wakes the old generator up instantly. The machine sputters like an old war horse before settling down to a rattle.
Cuno: "Yeah -- no." He quickly turns his attention back to the generator. "Cuno doesn't come here, I told you."
Inland Empire: 'It's cold now,' he was supposed to say. 'But someone has been maintaining it. The wiring has been repaired'...
Inland Empire: W-w-w-wait. Haven't you heard this before?
You: "What does this mean? A generator here?"
You: Where do these wires lead?
You: "What does this mean? A generator here?"
Kim Kitsuragi: He looks at the wall socket. "Downstairs somewhere."
He looks at the wall socket. "Downstairs, into the console, then from there into the room's electronics."
Microgrid Generator: The recoil start wakes the old generator up. The machine sputters like an old war horse before settling down to a rattle.
You: "Do *you* know anything about a fire guy?"
Cuno: "We're in. We're doing this," he says over the sputter.
Cuno: "Yeah, Cuno's fucking wise like that. Cuno's gonna be a real wise pig."
You: "I meant why is it here?"
You: "You have taught me the meaning of wisdom, Cuno."
Kim Kitsuragi: He nods approvingly. He even smiles.
Microgrid Generator: Downstairs somewhere -- or into the lighting perhaps? You can't tell.
Downstairs, into the console -- it's been established. From there they are distributed across the room...
Kim Kitsuragi: "I don't know. I am not a philosopher."
Microgrid Generator: The wind outside picks up suddenly with a faint howl. Inside it's warm.
Kim Kitsuragi: "The kind that's favoured by vagrants and fuel thieves. It's been a long winter... Long and cold."
Rhetoric: If anyone's stayed here, they'd need a generator.
Microgrid Generator: A hollow ring -- the canister is empty. Dust falls from the generator and down into the ammo lift.
Cuno: The boy helps you out, holding the canister up to the fuel tank as you tilt. Dark brown viscous fluid pours out and the room fills with a chemical smell.
Microgrid Generator: The recoil start wakes the old generator up. The machine sputters like an old war horse before settling down to a rattle.
Microgrid Generator: A tiny red light glitters inside the burnt plastic.
Kim Kitsuragi: "It's cold now," he concludes. "But someone has been maintaining it. The wiring has been repaired."
Pain Threshold: A small agony -- minuscule bones may have fractured -- but it proves the point.
You: "I am. This generator proves the universe is material..." (Kick the generator.)
Kim Kitsuragi: "Someone with basic electrical skills has restored it in order to keep the room warm. Maybe it's the *fire guy*..."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Someone with basic electrical skills has restored it in order to keep the room warm."
Microgrid Generator: The wind outside picks up suddenly with a faint howl. Inside it's warm.
Esprit de Corps: There's no time to dwell on this moment. You've got to keep moving...
Kim Kitsuragi: The lieutenant puts his hand on the metal barrel, checking for warmth...
You: "I meant why is it here?"
Microgrid Generator: The tank is far from full, but there should be enough inside to keep it going for a day.
Cuno: "Smells like *mazut*." The kid taps on the open fuel cap on the side of the dynamo. "Heavy fuel shit."
Inland Empire: But he's not here to say it. Something *else* got in the way. Events *intervened*...
Kim Kitsuragi: The lieutenant assists you, holding the canister up to the fuel tank as you tilt. Dark brown viscous fluid pours out and the room fills with a chemical smell.
Cuno: He looks at the wall socket. "Dunno, looks like downstairs somewhere..."
He looks at the wall socket. "Downstairs into that console we saw. And then to the rest of the room. Yeah. Electrical shit."
Inland Empire: N-n-n-no. This isn't right...
Kim Kitsuragi: "The kind that's favoured by vagrants and fuel thieves. It's been a long winter..."
Microgrid Generator: The industrial smell of *mazut* rises from the fuel cap. This generator uses heavy oil.
Microgrid Generator: There's a red starter switch on the side of the cylinder and a start rope on the other side -- the lieutenant flicks the switch.
Microgrid Generator: This old cylindrical generator waits with its fuel cap open. Makeshift electrical wiring runs out of its side and across the floor.
Conceptualization: That is his idea of a joke.
You: Pour fuel into the tank.
Conceptualization: Is it not the wisest man who knows he knows nothing?
Kim Kitsuragi: The lieutenant pauses. Something seems to be pecking at the edge of his concentration. He gives you a sideways look before adding...
Cuno: Cuno puts his hand on the generator. "This shit's cold."
Microgrid Generator: You brush away the thought and turn back to the generator.

Microgrid Generator: An old cylindrical generator is nested above the ammo lift, with makeshift electrical wiring running out of its side and across the floor. The cables disappear into the wall to your right.
You: What kind of generator am I looking at?
Microgrid Generator: The room fills with a pervasive chemical smell as dark brown liquid flows into the tank. There's a red starter switch on one side of the cylinder and a start rope on the other.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Liquid carbon, I would imagine it takes *mazut*." He points to the open fuel cap on the side of the dynamo.
Cuno: "Probably because it's winter. Some bums who camp here don't wanna freeze to death? Maybe? Probably. Cuno's probably right..."
